    <content>
        <layer>background</layer>
        <id>1</id>
        <text><span class="style2">download "http://the-ageless.com" to cd fld 1
	for each chunk put "downloading"
	when done answer "download finished"

	download internetAddress to globalContainerThis command starts a download of the contents of the URL given in internetAddress and, as the data arrives over the network, progressively writes it into the container given in globalContainer</span><span class="style3">. The download happens in the background, while other scripts continue executing, as such the container given must be one that exists beyond the duration of the current handler, like a global variable or a text field.
If you need to do something with the downloaded data besides displaying it in a text field, you can ask to be notified on completion in the following form:
</span><span class="style4">download </span><span class="style5">internetAddress</span><span class="style6"> to </span><span class="style7">globalContainer</span><span class="style8"> when done </span><span class="style9">command</span><span class="style10">or

	</span><span class="style11">download </span><span class="style12">internetAddress</span><span class="style13"> to </span><span class="style14">globalContainer</span><span class="style15">
		when done </span><span class="style16">command</span><span class="style17">

or

	</span><span class="style18">download </span><span class="style19">internetAddress</span><span class="style20"> to </span><span class="style21">globalContainer</span><span class="style22">
	when done
		</span><span class="style23">commands</span><span class="style24">
	end download</span><span class="style25">
or

	</span><span class="style26">download </span><span class="style27">internetAddress</span><span class="style28"> to </span><span class="style29">globalContainer</span><span class="style30"> when done
		</span><span class="style31">commands</span><span class="style32">
	end download</span><span class="style33">

Similarly, you can also be notified of the arrival of each new chunk of data, as it is transferred over the network:

	</span><span class="style34">download </span><span class="style35">internetAddress</span><span class="style36"> to </span><span class="style37">globalContainer</span><span class="style38"> for each chunk </span><span class="style39">command</span><span class="style40">
or

	</span><span class="style41">download </span><span class="style42">internetAddress</span><span class="style43"> to </span><span class="style44">globalContainer</span><span class="style45">
	for each chunk </span><span class="style46">command</span><span class="style47">
or

	</span><span class="style48">download </span><span class="style49">internetAddress</span><span class="style50"> to </span><span class="style51">globalContainer</span><span class="style52">
	for each chunk
		</span><span class="style53">commands</span><span class="style54">
	end download</span><span class="style55">
or

	</span><span class="style56">download </span><span class="style57">internetAddress</span><span class="style58"> to </span><span class="style59">globalContainer</span><span class="style60"> for each chunk
		</span><span class="style61">commands</span><span class="style62">
	end download</span><span class="style63">

You can also combine both forms to be notified of each time new data arrives, and when the download has completed:

	</span><span class="style64">download </span><span class="style65">internetAddress</span><span class="style66"> to </span><span class="style67">globalContainer</span><span class="style68">
	for each chunk
		</span><span class="style69">commands
	when done
		</span><span class="style70">commands
	end download</span><span class="style71">

etc.

</span><span class="style72">the download
</span><span class="style73">the download
	the totalSize of the download
	element "User-Agent" of the headers of the download</span><span class="style74">

Additional information on a download that is in progress is available to code inside the for each chunk or when done sections through the the download array. Currently, it contains the following keys:

</span><span class="style75">totalSize</span><span class="style76">			The size the download will have when finished, in bytes. May be -1 to indicate we won’t know until the download has finished</span><span class="style77">.
si</span><span class="style78">ze				The amount of data downloaded so far, in bytes</span><span class="style79">.
statusCo</span><span class="style80">de		The HTTP status code the web server returned, like 200 for success, or 404 for ‘file not foun</span><span class="style81">d’.
statusM</span><span class="style82">essage	A plain-text description of the statusCode, if avail</span><span class="style83">able.
a</span><span class="style84">ddress			The URL of the file downloaded. This is the same as the internetAddress you gave to the download com</span><span class="style85">mand.
h</span><span class="style86">eaders			An array containing the headers in the reply from the server, with the header name as the key, and the header value is the value associated with tha</span>t key.</text>
